text:
Anyone know if #python has an equivalent of #rstats's isTRUE? It returns TRUE only if the input is a single true value

isTRUE(T)

Not 2+ values

isTRUE(c(T, T))

Not anything non-boolean

isTRUE(1)
isTRUE("goober")
isTRUE(isTRUE)

Or missing

isTRUE(NULL)
isTRUE(NA)
isTRUE(NaN)

text:
#rstats 
HB <- function(p, alpha = 0.05){
  s <- sort(p)
  n <- length(s)
  r <- 1:n
  hb <- alpha/(n - r + 1)
  x <- s < hb
  if(all(s < hb)) return(alpha) else
  m <- min(which(x == F))
  s[m]
}
